            'file' => 'Idi_di_marzo_rovescio-2.jpg',
            'alt' => 'numismatic investment, Brutus denarius, Ides of March denarius',
            'link' => '__ROUTE:guide.faq__',
          ),
          'body' => '<b style="text-align: left;">Some considerations on numismatic investment</b><br><br><b>Precautions</b> – It is advisable to choose suppliers carefully; they should preferably be reputable companies and professionals. The widespread use of e-commerce for coins too calls for even greater care in selection. It is wise to request or have certifications carried out on purchased coins, attesting to their authenticity and condition. This precaution must be even stricter for ancient coins, for which purchase documents should always be kept to rebut the presumption, now particularly fashionable, of illegal archaeological provenance. Moreover, should you decide to divest this investment, the documentation gathered will make the coins offered even more appealing and sought after. If you have the “opportunity” to buy a coin from another collector or a small dealer, it is good practice to seek the opinion of a qualified expert at the time of the transaction.<br><b>Realisation</b> - Disposing of numismatic assets requires little time. The choice of which channel to use must also, in this case, be careful. For these aspects you can read our page: <a href="__ROUTE:sell.how__">how to sell</a>.',
